  "response": "If you are an XS in U.S. sizing, your Asian size would typically be around S or M, depending on the specific brand and country. Asian sizes often run smaller than U.S. sizes, so it's generally recommended to check the specific sizing charts of the brand you're interested in. Here's a general guideline:\n\n- U.S. XS is often equivalent to Asian size S (Small) or M (Medium).\n\nHowever, it's crucial to refer to the sizing chart provided by the specific retailer, as sizing can vary significantly across different brands and countries.",
